        <h2  class="recipe" id="PBJ">PB & J Sandwich</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Difficulty: 2/10</li>
            <li>Clean up: 3/10</li>
            <li>Taste: sweet and tasty</li>
            <li>Time: 10 minutes</li>
            <li>Serves: 1 person</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table id="ingredientsPBJ">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Bread</td>
                    <td>2 Cuts</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Peanut Butter</td>
                    <td>1 tablespoon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Jelly</td>
                    <td>1 tablespoon</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <h3 id="stepsPBJ" class="steps">Steps:</h3>
        <ol class="steps">
            <li>Toast both breads for about 2 minutes</li>
            <li>Take bread out of toaster</li>
            <li>Using a tool of choice spread peanut butter on one slice of bread</li>
            <li>Using a tool of choice spread the jelly on the other slice of bread</li>
            <li>Put two bread pieces together</li>
            <li>ENJOY!!!</li>
        </ol>
        
        <h2 id = "picturePBJ" class = "picture">Picture</h2>
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6a/Peanut-Butter-Jelly-Sandwich.png/250px-Peanut-Butter-Jelly-Sandwich.png" alt ="PBJ sandwich" width = "200">
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        <h2  class="recipe" id="omelette">Omelette</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Difficulty: 6/10</li>
            <li>Clean up: 7/10</li>
            <li>Taste: good and filling</li>
            <li>Time: 20 minutes</li>
            <li>Serves: 2 people</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table id="ingredientsOmelette">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Eggs</td>
                    <td>5</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Milk</td>
                    <td>1/5 cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Cheese</td>
                    <td>100 grams</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Tomato</td>
                    <td>1/8</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Salt</td>
                    <td>1/2 teaspoon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Parsley</td>
                    <td>10 grams</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <h3 id="stepsOmelette" class="steps">Steps:</h3>
        <ol class="steps">
            <li>Beat eggs in a bowl</li>
            <li>Pour in milk and mix</li>
            <li>Dice tomato into fine pieces</li>
            <li>Pour substance on to a medium hot buttered pan</li>
            <li>Scatter tomato all over omelette</li>
            <li>Add the cheese on top</li>
            <li>Cook until it seems cooked</li>
            <li>ENJOY!</li>
        </ol>
        
